## ‚ö†Ô∏è Important Context

### Design Considerations
- Mobile-first responsive design essential
- Accessibility compliance (WCAG 2.1 AA)
- Fast loading times for users on mobile data
- Clear calls-to-action for adoptions and donations

### Technical Decisions
- Static site generation for performance
- Tailwind CSS for consistent styling
- Markdown/MDX for content management
- No database needed initially (static content)

### Content Requirements
- Pet profiles with photos and descriptions
- Adoption application forms
- Volunteer sign-up forms
- Donation integration (Stripe/PayPal)
- Success stories and updates

## üí≠ Session Notes

This is a volunteer project for a registered animal rescue charity. Focus on:
- Clear, compassionate messaging
- Easy navigation for potential adopters
- Prominent donation options
- Mobile-optimized experience
- Fast, accessible design

The current live site (homelesshounds.com.au) can be referenced for content and features to migrate.

